 Sunday World has learnt that Mbalula had now slapped the Metro FM and SuperSport presenter with a lawsuit after Marawa allegedly ignored his letter of demand to apologise to the minister.Mbalula's lawyers from Maluleke, Msimang and Associates confirmed that they were dragging Marawa before judges at the South Gauteng High Court for a slew of remarks he has been making over the past two years about their client.One of the law firm's partners, Mikateko Shirilele, confirmed that they filed papers on April 12 after Marawa did not take their initial demands seriously for him to apologise to the minister.